Hi, Adam -

Are you able to take a &#39;jmap -histo&#39; of the crawler VM soon after the OOME?

There has been one OOME-related bug fixed since the 1.12.1 release that 
may be relevant:

http://webteam.archive.org/jira/browse/HER-1171

It is most likely to impact a crawl that either (A) encounters a domain 
with an essentially endless series of junk subdomains (so the 
&#39;inactiveQueues&#39; group grows without bound) or (B) &#39;retires&#39; a large 
number of queues which still contain URIs, rather than finishing them or 
clearing them out with scope/block rules.

If you have a working web UI on the affected crawl, what does the 
&#39;1-line&#39; frontier summary say about queue counts on the &#39;reports&#39; page? 
(That is, the parenthetical appearing aside the link to get a full 
frontier report.)

Unfortunately, the fix for HER-1171 is not checkpoint-compatible with 
1.12.1 crawls, so if you wanted to use a prerelease version of Heritrix 
with the fix you would have to restart from the recovery-logs.

- Gordon @ IA

